---
/**
 * context-engineering/0007 · Figure 3 — Module 1 HyDE "Embed the ANSWER's shape,
 * not the question's". Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg +
 * figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). Carries its own <defs> for the arrowhead
 * markers the shared top-of-body <svg> provided in the source.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A question and the answer document sit far apart in embedding space; a hypothetical answer lands near the real document."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Embed the ANSWER's shape, not the question's</text
        >
        <!-- question -->
        <circle cx="80" cy="86" r="22" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></circle><text
            x="80"
            y="89"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417">question</text
        >
        <!-- real doc -->
        <circle cx="520" cy="86" r="22" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
            x="520"
            y="83"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">answer</text
        ><text x="520" y="95" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >doc</text
        >
        <!-- hyde doc -->
        <circle cx="430" cy="86" r="22" fill="#f1eef2" stroke="#b5179e" stroke-width="2"
        ></circle><text
            x="430"
            y="89"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">HyDE doc</text
        >
        <!-- far arrow -->
        <line
            x1="102"
            y1="86"
            x2="404"
            y2="86"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <text x="250" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >far apart in vector space (different vocab)</text
        >
        <!-- near arrow -->
        <line x1="452" y1="86" x2="496" y2="86" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <text x="430" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#b5179e"
            >LLM drafts a fake answer &rarr; embed THAT &rarr; lands next to the real doc</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Questions and answers use different words, so the question's embedding sits far from the
        document that answers it. HyDE has the LLM draft a plausible answer and embeds <em>that</em> —
        even a partly-wrong draft has the right <em>shape</em> to retrieve the real source.<sup
            ><a href="#s2" id="r2b">2</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
